In [[rocket]]ry, the '''Goddard problem''' is to optimize the [[altitude]] of a rocket, ascending vertically, and taking into account [[atmospheric drag]] and the [[gravitational field]].  This was first posed by [[Robert H. Goddard]] in his 1919 publication, "A Method of Reaching Extreme Altitudes".<ref>http://www.aoe.vt.edu/~cliff/aoe5244_99/week_13_a.pdf</ref><ref>http://oai.dtic.mil/oai/oai?verb=getRecord&metadataPrefix=html&identifier=AD0409855</ref>

